## Brand rules (AppyDave — typography-first)

- Palette occupies 80%+ of the frame: brown #342d2d, gold #ccba9d, yellow #ffde59, plus cream #faf5ec OR dark-surface #25201e as ground
- Yellow is reserved for the hook text or ONE attention element
- Brown is a first-class ground colour (panels, pills, split layouts encouraged)
- Hook text: Bebas Neue, uppercase, 2–5 words, left-aligned, 30–60% frame width, composed INTO the image at generation time (never baked in second)
- Every thumbnail carries a ghost watermark in Oswald or Bebas Neue: bold, uppercase, brown @ 8–15% opacity on cream OR cream @ 6–12% on dark brown, bleeds off at least one edge, sits behind the hook text
- One of five composition patterns: Type-Dominant / Type + Glyph / Split Panel / Sequence Badge / Ghost-Forward
- Anti-patterns: NO humans, NO halftone/newsprint/comic-book outlines, NO 3D render/photorealism, NO neon colours, NO small text (<40px cap height at 1280×720), NO post-bake overlays

## Brief shape

For each of the 3 selected titles, produce 2 design briefs (totalling 6) that differ in composition pattern or angle. Each brief must:
- Specify a single composition pattern
- Specify ground colour (cream or dark brown)
- Specify ghost watermark word + edge-bleed direction + opacity
- Specify hook text exact words + colour (must use one of the canonical text-on-ground pairings)
- Specify any glyph or panel layout if used
- Carry `title_ref` = the title text exactly as it appears in selectedTitles

